It doesn't make sense to differentiate here between `.size() == 1` and ` > 1` when you are treating them the same otherwise.
You can just write it as

```java
            for (String entry : nameProps) {
                if (entry.contains(NAME)) {
                    name = entry;
                    hasName = true;
                }
            }
```

I think.
Also the question is if you should `break` the loop once you have a match.
Because right now, you are reassigning `name` and thus skip over a few values without actually doing something with them.
But of course it may be possible that you actually want the "last matching" name in the list...

Can't we invoke `execute(args);` here instead of

```java
        ReindexingTool reindexingTool = new ReindexingTool();
        reindexingTool.execute(args);
```

Because `new ReindexingTool()` in the constructor would kind of create some infinite recursion here, wouldn't it? 😄
